mono is compose, and we'll see that.

11
00:00:34.250 --> 00:00:36.790
But if you have to use
a monad in your application,

12
00:00:36.790 --> 00:00:40.990
which is typically the case,
these things don't actually compose.

13
00:00:40.990 --> 00:00:43.932
So, we focus on normalizing the shape,

14
00:00:43.932 --> 00:00:49.131
kind of mashing them into the one
thing like the inside of a gobstopper.

15
00:00:49.131 --> 00:00:51.241
